Ask HN: Aren’t high Egress fees clearly anti competitive?
text: I think we are all used to the various cloud providers having very high egress fees. The reason for that being that it leads to a very strong lock in to the cloud providers services. Want to use some processing using your own servers on data in GCS or S3 ? Good luck. Isn’t that clearly anti competitive and should be regulated ?

Ask HN: IoT to Detect Noise and Outlaws?
text:
I live in a place where noise has increased exponentially over the past 2 years. Many elderly people living in my building upset by these events.

There are people accelerating their motorbikes and powerful cars madly, at dawn and I would like to prove these to my city hall so that they can take some action, because this is killing our sleep on a daily basis.

How would you approach a project like this using microcontrollers like arduino or raspberry, in terms of modules and ideas?

I live in a corner building, on the first floor, with a diagonal view of the avenue where the kids are playing with their toys.

Show HN: Trigger Webhooks from Postgres
text:
We just released a small open-source tool which enables you to fire HTTP requests from Postgres triggers.

One of the things we’re using it for now is to send Slack messages when a new user is created and wanted to see what the community thinks as we explore more use cases!
